**Describe the bug**
While working on the method for safe un-shimming in #6555  I noticed that jdeps reveals we have public->spark3xx-common dependencies that may lead to classloading bugs

```Bash
grep '(spark3' public.dot 
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.AvroProvider (public)"             -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.RapidsConf (spark3xx-common)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.AvroProvider (public)"             -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.ScanRule (spark3xx-common)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.AvroProvider (public)"             -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.SparkPlanMeta (spark3xx-common)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.AvroProvider (public)"             -> "org.apache.spark.sql.rapids.GpuFileSourceScanExec (spark330)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.HiveProvider (public)"             -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.DataWritingCommandRule (spark3xx-common)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.HiveProvider (public)"             -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.ExprRule (spark3xx-common)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.ShimLoader (public)"               -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.Optimizer (spark3xx-common)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.ShimLoader$ (public)"              -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.Optimizer (spark3xx-common)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.SparkShims (public)"               -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.CoalesceSizeGoal (spark3xx-common)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.SparkShims (public)"               -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.ExecRule (spark3xx-common)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.SparkShims (public)"               -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.ExprRule (spark3xx-common)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.SparkShims (public)"               -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.ScanRule (spark3xx-common)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.SparkShims (public)"               -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.SparkPlanMeta (spark3xx-common)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.iceberg.IcebergProvider (public)"  -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.ScanRule (spark3xx-common)";
   "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.iceberg.IcebergProvider (public)"  -> "com.nvidia.spark.rapids.iceberg.IcebergProvider$ (spark3xx-common)";
```
